This paper presents a new dataset and user simulator for testing an agent's ability to read an ambiguous text, ask questions, and provide explanations. The focus on natural language understanding and reasoning suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of neural architecture and end-to-end memory networks further supports these categories. The paper also involves reasoning and question-answering, which could place it in the categories of Computation and Language (cs.CC) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
